  - benchmark
  - synthetic-data
abstract: >
  Penumbra is a privacy-preserving perpetual multi-agent arena where
  N=20-50 agents compete on a procedurally dynamic graph. Agent state
  is encrypted at rest and in transit; a live dashboard streams
  encrypted aggregates, statistical inference summaries, and on-chain
  match-outcome proofs. The codebase ships a teaching platform, the
  Penumbra-Bench evaluation suite (5 tasks across privacy, adversarial
  resilience, multi-agent cooperation, privacy-budget management, and
  linkability resistance), and the Penumbra-Data synthetic dataset
  family (4 tiers, 7 modalities, CC-BY-4.0).
